#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:145
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"In this section, we'll take a good look at disk-oriented aspects of Linux,\n"
"including Linux filesystems, partitions, and block devices. Once you're familar\n"
"with the ins and outs of disks and filesystems, we'll guide you through the\n"
"process of setting up partitions and filesystems on Linux.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:152
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To begin, I'll introduce \"block devices\". The most famous block device is\n"
"probably the one that represents the first IDE drive in a Linux system:\n"
msgstr ""

