#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:382
#, no-wrap
msgid "Sample partition commentary"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:386
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"In our suggested \"newbie\" partition configuration, we have three partitions.\n"
"The first one (<path>/dev/hda1</path>) at the beginning of the disk is a small\n"
"partition called a boot partition. The boot partition's purpose is to hold all\n"
"the critical data related to booting -- GRUB boot loader information (if you\n"
"will be using GRUB) as well as your Linux kernel(s). The boot partition gives\n"
"us a safe place to store everything related to booting Linux. During normal\n"
"day-to-day Linux use, your boot partition should remain unmounted for safety.\n"
"If you are setting up a SCSI system, your boot partition will likely end up\n"
"being <path>/dev/sda1</path>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:398
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"It's recommended to have boot partitions (containing everything necessary for\n"
"the boot loader to work) at the beginning of the disk. While not necessarily\n"
"required anymore, it is a useful tradition from the days when the LILO boot\n"
"loader wasn't able to load kernels from filesystems that extended beyond disk\n"
"cylinder 1024.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:406
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The second partition (<path>/dev/hda2</path>) s used for swap space. The kernel\n"
"uses swap space as virtual memory when RAM becomes low. This partition,\n"
"relatively speaking, isn't very big either, typically somewhere around 512 MB.\n"
"If you're setting up a SCSI system, this partition will likely end up being\n"
"called <path>/dev/hda2</path>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:414
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The third partition (<path>/dev/hda3</path>) is quite large and takes up the\n"
"rest of the disk. This partition is called our root partition and will be used\n"
"to store your main filesystem that houses the main Linux filesystem. On a SCSI\n"
"system, this partition would likely end up being <path>/dev/hda3</path>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:423
#, no-wrap
msgid "Getting started"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:427
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Okay, now to create the partitions as in the example and table above. First,\n"
"enter fdisk by typing <c>fdisk /dev/hda</c> or <c>fdisk /dev/sda</c>, depending\n"
"on whether you're using IDE or SCSI. Then, type <c>p</c> to view your\n"
"current partition configuration. Is there anything on the disk that you need to\n"
"keep? If so, stop now. If you continue with these directions, all existing data\n"
"on your disk will be erased.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><impo>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:436
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Following the instructions below will cause all prior data on your disk to be\n"
"erased! If there is anything on your drive, please be sure that it is\n"
"non-critical information that you don't mind losing. Also make sure that you\n"
"have selected the correct drive so that you don't mistakenly wipe data from the\n"
"wrong drive.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:446
#, no-wrap
msgid "Zapping existing partitions"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:450
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now, it's time to delete any existing partitions. To do this, type d and hit\n"
"enter. You will then be prompted for the partition number you would like to\n"
"delete. To delete a pre-existing <path>/dev/hda1</path>, you would type:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:455
#, no-wrap
msgid "Deleting pre-existing partition"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:456
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Command (m for help): <i>d</i>\n"
"Partition number (1-4): <i>1</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:461
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The partition has been scheduled for deletion. It will no longer show up if you\n"
"type <c>p</c>, but it will not be erased until your changes have been saved. If\n"
"you made a mistake and want to abort without saving your changes, type <c>q</c>\n"
"immediately and hit enter and your partition will not be deleted.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:468
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now, assuming that you do indeed want to wipe out all the partitions on your\n"
"system, repeatedly type <c>p</c> to print out a partition listing and then type\n"
"<c>d</c> and the number of the partition to delete it. Eventually, you'll end\n"
"up with a partition table with nothing in it:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:474
#, no-wrap
msgid "Drives look after cleaning it"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:476
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Disk /dev/hda: 30.0 GB, 30005821440 bytes\n"
"240 heads, 63 sectors/track, 3876 cylinders\n"
"Units = cylinders of 15120 * 512 = 7741440 bytes\n"
"\n"
"Device Boot    Start       End    Blocks   Id  System\n"
"\n"
"Command (m for help):\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:488
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:500
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating a boot partition"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:492
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now that the in-memory partition table is empty, we're ready to create a boot\n"
"partition. To do this, type <c>n</c> to create a new partition, then <c>p</c>\n"
"to tell fdisk you want a primary partition. Then type <c>1</c> to create the\n"
"first primary partition. When prompted for the first cylinder, hit enter. When\n"
"prompted for the last cylinder, type <c>+100M</c> to create a partition 100MB\n"
"in size. Here's the output from these steps:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:501
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Command (m for help): <i>n</i>\n"
"Command action\n"
"e   extended\n"
"p   primary partition (1-4)\n"
"<i>p</i>\n"
"Partition number (1-4): <i>1</i>\n"
"First cylinder (1-3876, default 1):\n"
"Using default value 1\n"
"Last cylinder or +size or +sizeM or +sizeK (1-3876, default 3876): <i>+100M</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:513
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now, when you type <c>p</c>, you should see the following partition printout:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:516
#, no-wrap
msgid "Partition printout"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:517
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Command (m for help): <i>p</i>\n"
"\n"
"Disk /dev/hda: 30.0 GB, 30005821440 bytes\n"
"240 heads, 63 sectors/track, 3876 cylinders\n"
"Units = cylinders of 15120 * 512 = 7741440 bytes\n"
"\n"
"   Device Boot    Start       End    Blocks   Id  System\n"
"/dev/hda1             1        14    105808+  83  Linux\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:530
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating the swap partition"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:534
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Next, let's create the swap partition. To do this, type <c>n</c> to create a\n"
"new partition, then <c>p</c> to tell fdisk that you want a primary partition.\n"
"Then type <c>2</c> to create the second primary partition,\n"
"<path>/dev/hda2</path> in our case. When prompted for the first cylinder, hit\n"
"enter. When prompted for the last cylinder, type <c>+512M</c> to create a\n"
"partition 512MB in size. After you've done this, type <c>t</c> to set the\n"
"partition type, and then type <c>82</c> to set the partition type to \"Linux\n"
"Swap.\" After completing these steps, typing <c>p</c> should display a partition\n"
"table that looks similar to this:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:545
#, no-wrap
msgid "Partition table"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:546
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Command (m for help): <i>p</i>\n"
"\n"
"Disk /dev/hda: 30.0 GB, 30005821440 bytes\n"
"240 heads, 63 sectors/track, 3876 cylinders\n"
"Units = cylinders of 15120 * 512 = 7741440 bytes\n"
"\n"
"   Device Boot    Start       End    Blocks   Id  System\n"
"/dev/hda1             1        14    105808+  83  Linux\n"
"/dev/hda2            15        81    506520   82  Linux swap\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:560
#, no-wrap
msgid "Making it bootable"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:564
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Finally, we need to set the \"bootable\" flag on our boot partition and then\n"
"write our changes to disk. To tag <path>/dev/hda1</path> as a \"bootable\"\n"
"partition, type <c>a</c> at the menu and then type 1 for the partition number.\n"
"If you type <c>p</c> now, you'll now see that <path>/dev/hda1</path> has an \"*\"\n"
"in the \"Boot\" column. Now, let's write our changes to disk. To do this, type\n"
"<c>w</c> and hit enter. Your disk partitions are now properly configured for\n"
"the installation of Linux.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:574
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If fdisk instructs you to do so, please reboot to allow your system to detect\n"
"the new partition configuration.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:581
#, no-wrap
msgid "Extended and logical partitioning"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:585
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"In the above example, we created a single primary partition that will contain a\n"
"filesystem used to store all our data. This means that after installing Linux,\n"
"this main filesystem will get mounted at \"<path>/</path>\" and will contain a\n"
"tree of directories that contain all our files.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:592
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"While this is a common way to set up a Linux system, there is another approach\n"
"that you should be familiar with. This approach uses multiple partitions that\n"
"house multiple filesystems and are then \"linked\" together to form a cohesive\n"
"filesystem tree. For example, it is common to put <path>/home</path> and\n"
"<path>/var</path> on their own filesystems.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:600
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"We could have made hda2 into an extended rather than a primary partition. Then,\n"
"we could have created the hda5, hda6, and hda7 logical partitions (which would\n"
"technically be contained \"inside\" hda2), which would house the <path>/</path>,\n"
"<path>/home</path>, and <path>/var</path> filesystems respectively.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:607
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You can learn more about these types of multi-filesystem configurations by\n"
"studying the resources listed on the next page.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:614
#, no-wrap
msgid "Partitioning resources"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:618
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"For more information on partitioning, take a look at the following partitioning\n"
"tips:\n"
