#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:1657
#, no-wrap
msgid "Digging in: GRUB"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:1661
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The GRUB boot loader could be considered the next generation of boot loader,\n"
"following LILO. Most visibly to users, it provides a menu interface instead of\n"
"LILO's primitive prompt. For system administrators, the changes are more\n"
"significant. GRUB supports more operating systems than LILO, provides some\n"
"password-based security in the boot menu, and is easier to administer.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:1669
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"GRUB is usually installed with the <c>grub-install</c> command. Once installed,\n"
"GRUB's menu is administrated by editing the file\n"
"<path>/boot/grub/grub.conf</path>. Both of these tasks are beyond the scope of\n"
"this document; you should read the GRUB info pages before attempting to install\n"
"or administrate GRUB.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:1679
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using GRUB"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:1683
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To give parameters to the kernel, you can press <c>e</c> at the boot menu. This\n"
"provides you with the opportunity to edit (by again pressing <c>e</c>) either\n"
"the name of the kernel to load or the parameters passed to it. When you're\n"
"finished editing, press &lt;enter&gt; then <c>b</c> to boot with your changes.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:1692
#, no-wrap
msgid "dmesg"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:1696
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The boot messages from the kernel and init scripts typically scroll by quickly.\n"
"You might notice an error, but it's gone before you can properly read it. In\n"
"that case, there are two places you can look after the system boots to see what\n"
"went wrong (and hopefully get an idea how to fix it).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:1703
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If the error occurred while the kernel was loading or probing hardware devices,\n"
"you can retrieve a copy of the kernel's log using the <c>dmesg</c> command:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:1707
#, no-wrap
msgid "Retrieving kernel's log using dmesg command"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:1712
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Hey, we recognize that line! It's the first line the kernel prints when it\n"
"loads. Indeed, if you pipe the output of <c>dmesg</c> into a pager, you can\n"
"view all of the messages the kernel printed on boot, plus any messages the\n"
"kernel has printed to the console in the meantime. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:1721
#, no-wrap
msgid "/var/log/messages"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:1725
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The second place to look for information is in the\n"
"<path>/var/log/messages</path> file. This file is recorded by the syslog\n"
"daemon, which accepts input from libraries, daemons, and the kernel. Each line\n"
"in the messages file is timestamped. This file is a good place to look for\n"
"errors that occurred during the init scripts stage of booting. For example, to\n"
"see the last few messages from the nameserver:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:1733
#, no-wrap
msgid "greping /var/log/messages file"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/articles/lpi-101-advanced-p4.xml:1734
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>grep named /var/log/messages | tail -3</i>\n"
"Jan 12 20:17:41 time /usr/sbin/named[350]: listening on IPv4 interface lo, 127.0.0.1#53\n"
"Jan 12 20:17:41 time /usr/sbin/named[350]: listening on IPv4 interface eth0, 10.0.0.1#53\n"
"Jan 12 20:17:41 time /usr/sbin/named[350]: running\n"
